$ Oracle: V$SGA_DYNAMIC_COMPONENTS
@ v$sga_dynamic_components

`v$sga_dynamic_components`: information about sga resize operations since startup.
-
This view can also be used to find out the granule size of → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA components. 

`v$sga_dynamic_components` shows excatly the same information as `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/memory/dynamic_components` except that it does not include
the two rows for `SGA Target` and `PGA Target`.
-
Both views select from `x$kmgsct`.

